The calculation of estimates for construction projects in the Russian Federation will take place in a new way
Issues of pricing, regulation of the construction industry, as well as problems of connecting to networks, the Federal Antimonopoly Service takes special control.
An expert council for the development of competition in the construction industry has been established under the Federal Antimonopoly Service.
At its meeting, Vadim Solovyov, head of the department for control of housing and communal services, construction and natural resources of the Federal Antimonopoly Service, said that &quot;today&#39;s calculation of estimates for construction projects is absolutely incomprehensible.&quot;
The regulatory framework makes pricing opaque and can lead to unreasonable construction costs, according to the FAS.
And they propose to determine the cost of construction of state-owned objects at the design stage on the basis of market prices for constructive solutions instead of the estimated norms and unit prices for technological operations used today.
These proposals have been included in the &quot;road map&quot; and are now under consideration by the Ministry of Construction.
&quot;Replacing traditional estimate documentation in construction with calculations of structural elements should lead to less corruption in the industry,&quot; Vadim Solovyov explained to RSL.
Indeed, now every bolt and nut is calculated in the estimate, and it is not always possible to check everything, therefore sometimes unscrupulous construction companies can bury &quot;whole tractors&quot; in the documentation.
The Ministry of Construction agrees with the FAS.
“The first developments on the transition to cost calculation by structural elements are already in place: methods have been developed for calculating prices for structural solutions, drawing up estimates for these indicators,” Elena Zhukova, head of the department of urban planning and architecture of the Ministry of Construction, told RSL.
The field of road construction was chosen as a pilot project.
However, experts believe that the problem is much more serious.
Anatoly Demyanko, the head of the construction company Profi-invest, told RGB that the estimated standards are outdated long ago, but no other mechanism has yet been offered to business.
&quot;As for the proposed calculations for structural elements, in practice it is difficult to implement, since completely different technologies are often used in the construction of buildings,&quot; he said.
It is no secret that the construction market is developing largely thanks to government orders.
According to Ekaterina Lezina, chairman of the board of the NP &quot;Expert community of state order professionals&quot;, today the state is the most solvent customer.
Vladimir Malakhov, Deputy Director for Engineering at Rosatom’s Industry Center for Capital Construction, drew attention to the fact that today the market is conditionally divided into companies that have access to a portfolio of contracts, and companies that have monopoly competencies and do not allow competitors to enter this field.
He believes that the creation of a transparent market is possible only if access to contracts is protected as much as possible from someone&#39;s control influence.
At the expert council, it was proposed to form a system of state orders in such a way that the same contractor is not entitled to receive more than one contract worth more than 1 billion rubles. or several contracts worth more than 1 billion rubles.
The Ministry of Construction believes that this approach should be evaluated in terms of the impact on business, as well as the effectiveness of construction management.
As Elena Zhukova explained, in this case, it will be necessary to give the customer the functions of a general contractor, which will lead to an increase in the customer&#39;s staffing level and budget costs for its maintenance.
At the same time, the customer&#39;s specialists will have to have the knowledge to assess the quality of work performed by contractors, as well as their safety.
Often, this breakdown will need to determine who will be responsible for the security of the site as a whole.
In addition, this approach may lead to an outflow of highly qualified participants in public procurement due to lack of interest in obtaining a state order for an incomplete scope of work and a small contract amount.
Alexander Yevstashenkov, deputy head of the Expert Advisory Center of the Procurement Institute, believes that now the state order procedure has turned into a business game for the contractor&#39;s attentiveness.
And he gave such an example: &quot;when filling out the application, the participant must indicate&quot; specific indicators &quot;without specifying the words: &quot;or equivalent&quot;, &quot;should be&quot;, &quot;from&quot;, &quot;more&quot;, &quot;less&quot;, &quot;analogue&quot;, &quot;or&quot;, &quot;type&quot;, &quot;similar type&quot;, &quot;not lower&quot;, &quot;lower&quot;, &quot;higher&quot;, &quot;may&quot;, &quot;may have&quot;, &quot;may be&quot;, &quot;earlier&quot;, &quot;not earlier&quot;, &quot;not higher&quot;, &quot;not allowed&quot;, etc.
Thus, customers often abuse their right to set requirements for the content of the application submitted by contractors.
Another problem of 44-FZ, according to Yevstashenkov, was the need to assess the quality of work through the participant&#39;s &quot;paper&quot; proposal even at the stage of filing an application.
Considering the application of the participant, it is really possible to evaluate only the qualifications of the contractor, but not the quality of the work, which has not even been started yet, - the expert believes.
The quality of the work can only be assessed upon acceptance.
It was also proposed at the expert council to shift marginal income from the upper to the lower echelon so that intermediate contractors disappear.
Chairman of the Expert Council, State Secretary, Deputy Head of the FAS Andrei Tsarikovskiy believes that this should not be done, since the general contractor should be responsible for the order.
Otherwise, it will turn out, as in the well-known reprise of Arkady Raikin&#39;s &quot;Atelier&quot;: &quot;Do you have any complaints about the buttons?&quot;
