According to Russian news reports on his remarks, Russian President Vladimir Putin demanded on Sunday that the Ukrainian government stop fighting separatists in the country&#39;s east and immediately begin talks on &quot;statehood&quot; for the breakaway region.
His spokesman, Dmitry Peskov, later clarified that Putin did not mean to imply that separatist-controlled eastern Ukrainian territory would become part of Russia, but that its status within Ukraine needed to be revised to allow the Russian-speaking region to defend its rights and interests.
